            <div class="container vanta-bg-event">
                <br><br>
                <header class="header">
                    <h1> MATH PIRATES </h1>
                    <marquee class="marqueedesk" behavior="" direction=""> Hoist the anchor and set the sail for a math
                        adventure! </marquee>
                    <p class="marqueemob"> Hoist the anchor and set the sail for a math adventure! </p>
                    <p class="para-indent">Do you want to explore the high seas and improve your math skills !?...
                        Come join the math pirates crew, flaunt your quick wit and become the
                        ultimate math pirateâ€¦from addition to navigation, our quiz will set
                        you on a math adventure like no other!</p>

                    <div class="social-container">
                        <i class="fa-regular fa-envelope"></i> &nbsp;20pw16@psgtech.ac.in<br />
                        <i class="fa-regular fa-envelope"></i> &nbsp;20pw23@psgtech.ac.in
                    </div>
                </header>
                <div class="main-content">
                    <div class="agenda">
                        <h2>Event Details</h2>

                        <div class="sessions">
                            <div class="session">
                                <span class="session-head"> Round 1 : <span class="event-mode">Prelims</span></span>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>This round features a computer-based general math quiz, comprising questions that assess aptitude, reasoning, quick calculation skills, and general math intuition.</li>
                                    <li>There will be 30 questions in total. </li>
                                    <li>Each question carries 1 mark. <b>No negative marking.</b></li>
                                    <li>The time duration for completing the test by each team will be noted and will be used in case of tie.</li>
                                    <li><b>6 Teams</b> will be shortlisted for the next round.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="session">
                                <span class="session-head"> Round 2 : <span class="event-mode">Finals</span></span>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Has three sub rounds</li>
                                    <ol class="event-mode">
                                        <li>Roll 'n' Solve</li>
                                        <li>Cipher Quest</li>
                                        <li>Fast and furious.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                </ul>
                                <ol>
                                    <br>
                                    <li> Roll 'n' Solve </li>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>A total of 36 numbered tiles, ranging from (1,1) to (6,6), are presented. </li>
                                        <li>Each player is required to roll the dice twice, and subsequently, solve the question situated beneath the tile that corresponds to the numbers obtained from the first and second rolls.</li>
                                        <li>Throughout the quiz, each team will be allocated a total of six questions to answer.</li>
                                        <li>Each correct answer is awarded 5 marks.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <br>
                                    <li> Cipher Quest</li>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Upon uncovering a hidden QR Code beneath a set of 2x2 covered tiles, players will progressively answer a series of four questions.</li>
                                        <li>Each answered question will serve as an input for the subsequent question, and upon answering each question, a corresponding tile will be flipped to reveal a portion of the QR Code.</li>
                                        <li>Ultimately, the complete QR Code will be revealed, and players will be required to solve a fifth and final question by scanning the fully disclosed QR Code.</li>
                                        <li>Each correct answer for the tile carries 5 marks, the question solved by scanning the QR carries 10 marks.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <br>
                                    <li> Fast and Furious</li>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>It is a rapid-fire round.</li>
                                        <li>Each team will be given 1 minute to answer the questions.</li>
                                        <li>For each correct answer 5 marks will be awarded</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </ol>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="details">
                        <div class="register closed">
